Nick, Amanda, and Josh all came to my house after school it was tres fun. YAY, for Nick carting them to my house!

OK, so me and Amanda are right now having a conversation about nuns, and it's rather funny.

 pyroshinobi89 [4:55 PM]:  we should work at the same places...t'would be insanity in its finest most pure form. ...Also known as Amanda.

We have the same idea. o_o

So anyways, school was alright today. Me and Jake were stupid and giggly all day. But last night he and Katie broke up and I felt way bad. Music Theory was fun, I got to be the whistler, because Hannah doesn't have whistling skills.

Well, yarr. School seems like it's going to be el fun this year. xD Me and Kelsey were trying to find out our french names and made Christopher go with Coco Griswald Beaumont LeBeouf. XD I'm going with Rayna, because that sounds like a videogame character, and then Kelsey is probably Chantal again. French rocks everyone. xD

El-jay update pt. 1:

School has started. Oh joy! Actually, it's not half bad, and i'm actually taking Nick's advice and going in with a positive attitude. I've got all good classes save for Biology, which isn't necisarilly bad, it's just got a few douchebags in it. But all is good. Then i've got S/F, and music theory with Jake-Pants, and Handark. French with Kelsey. Math with Erich and Lindsey. Overall, this should be a good year, and i'm actually quite happy. I'm actually going to have to do extra shit in school this year also (x_x) Mr. Carter basically assaulted me in the hall telling me to do Speech stuff, and I might do it, because it could be fun. Also, my parental units are like "Swimming for you!!", and I guess i'm alright with it. :|

Other than school and stuff, I have a few concerts coming up, which is mad awesome. Like i've mentioned sixty five times before, i'm going to see System of a Down, then Slipknot again, and then, HOPEFULLY, Children of Bodom, since they're coming to Chicago! That's the one i'm uber excited about. Amanda said she heard stuff about DeG coming to America! Very cool also.

So.. UM.. yarr.

El-Jay update pt. 2

I'm warning you now, this is a rant. Please direct yourself away if you don't care.

Alright, so my Dad is already on my case about school. Oh wow. It's Wednesday we started on fucking MONDAY! My Dad also got me a car (Honda Accord, thanks. xD), I mean, that's flipping amazing. But he's already gone off on "You know that those keys are going away so quick if your grades are bad." My Mom told me he was in a bad mood, and not to get in arguments with him, but I couldn't help it because he was the one who kept bugging me about it, so I just kind of went "I KNOW, ALRIGHT!" and he was like "Well, if you're going to be like that.." and I just felt like.. oh, shit. x_x I felt bad, but he shouldn't be on my case about school so soon, I signed up for all these goddamned high track classes so he wouldn't bother me. He also said something like "I would say I trust you to get good grades, but after last year, I can't say I trust you." What the hell.

End of rant.

Well, alright. I'm OK, now! So, anyways. Yay for LJ.

 

(..and, Lisa.. back off my icons. xD)

Ticket and backstage pass? Whoot.

Slash rocks. Sweet hair, indeed.

Sort of resembling... something weird.

My failed attempt at a good picture of Scott Weiland..

Slash playing his amazing guitar.

K, so tonight was Velvet Revolver. OMGWTFBBQ.DSG.KDFJGDSLSD. I met them. I MET THEM. Slash is so fucking awesome. We had our pictures taken with them, but we have to wait until they send.

The concert was flipping amazing. Second best this year. :O We were really close. :) I can't talk, my knees hurt, my neck is dying. But it's alright. 

Sweet picture update later.

EDIT: Amanda who is awesome hxc is also coming to Velvet Revolver. Teapots, and scrabble, and ...here's to us having crazy times?

Ok. School starts the 22nd, what the freakin' heck?! Where has summer gone.. It's sort of depressing for me. I really do dislike school. Especially since a large amount of the people at Glenwood are assholes.. Oh well. But on a good note, there are a few people I can stand. ;)

Tomorrow will effing OWN, though. I'm probably going to wake up a little early, and go swimming. Then around fivish, Nick, Jake, Katie, and I, are all going to go and see Velvet Revolver. Yesss. It's going to fucking rock. Slash is god.

 

Things I should probably do this school year, but most likely won't:

  • Do my homework.
  • Stop disliking people.
  • Stop hating my teachers.
  • Learn how to make people feel better..
  • Learn how to deal with Kim complaining alot.(Edit: I love Kim. Like.. alot.)
  • Get good grades.
  • See more concerts. x)

WELL. Whoot. I'm bored.

My day was pretty sweet, even if it was sort of boring..

It has consisted of swimming, school hating, and gravel. :D

My Mom woke me up around some time to go swimming, and I was like.. well, fine. So I went swimming and Ryan, Amanda, Sean, and Mimi were all there, we talked for about fifteen minutes, but David called Ryan and they were all going over to Guzzardo's house, EW. I don't do well with that kid. Kelsey punched him once. :) Hah. So Mimi stayed with me, because obviously, she doesn't like him either. Yay for Mimi. Then she left and then we left. Woohoo.

Then we came home, and me and my Fajah went and rented movies (Constantine, Hitch, and the new Crow movie), I drove, and it was sweet. Except for on the way home, you have to drive on this road that isn't in really good condition and there is loose gravel everywhere, and since i'm a speed-demon (xD, no.) I took the turn at 30, which is what I usually do anyways, and I spun out. It was hysterical, and my Dad was laughing at me because I was screaming "IT WASN'T MY FAULT." If my Mom would have been in the car, she would have died. xD

Well, i'm done.

Kbye.

K, so this entry will have rantage, and.. other amusing things. 


Alright, so last night I'm sitting in my room talking to Nick, and all the sudden 6 people enter my house. :| It was weird, and then I guess my Mom went upstairs to see who was up there and there was a half naked kid.. I thought it was damn funny.. but obviously my Mom was just kind of disturbed, and weirded out. xD

So I woke up this morning, and me and Casey kinda planned to go to the south park show together, and swing and have fun and such. I had it all planned out on how I was going to get there, and how I was going to get home, I told my Mom, it was all good. But then she decides that were all going swimming, and I can't go anymore, and I had to call Casey and tell her I couldn't go. :( It was sad, and I didn't like it.

THEN, after swimming, which turned out to be not so bad, Amanda W. wanted me to go over to her house afterwards and hang out with her, Mimi, Sean, Ryan (Omg, yeah. Turns out the kid doesn't hate me. Although i'm having extreme trust issues with him anyways, because he's one of those kids who changes around his friends), Kelsea, and others. I get there, everyone hadn't even shown up, my Mom shows up FIFTEEN MINUTES LATER, and tells me I have to leave. I mean, why the FUCK would you tell me I could go hang out with my friends house for fifteen minutes?! Ugh. Lame.

Both things happened because she doesn't like to give me rides anywhere. :) So, I want a car. Lol. Oh well, gotta deal with it.

So ummmm. Yeah.

Ok. School starts soon. UGH UGH UGH UGH UGH. :)

Casey's away message reminded me... DAMN YOU, WOMAN!!
 
Nick's leaving tomorrow, for somewhere. :( But it'll be OK.

So tomorrow, i'm probably going to see Indecision and all those other bands at South Park. I don't know how good the show is going to be, but I wanna go, so yay.

I don't know what i'm doing on Monday or Tuesday, so if you want to call me, go for it.

But Wednesday i'm going to six flags or something.

Also might see Disturbed. Not as exciting.. but it'll be fun, I think. xD
